ces Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu ROTC Leadership Air Force ROTC Home Courses Info for Current Cadets Info for Prospective Cadets VMI AF Hall of Fame Faculty Capt  Mark A  Smith Recruiting Flight Commander  540 464 7587 AFROTC P   540  464 7354 F   540  464 7775 Virginia Military Institute 2018 Kilbourne Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact AFROTC Current as of  27 Jan  2016   Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Leadership   Air Force ROTC   Beaver  Theresa Major Theresa Beaver Maj Theresa Beaver is the Operations Officer for the Reserve Officer Training Corps  Detachment 880 at the Virginia Military Institute in Lexington  Virginia  She supervises unit operations  recruiting  and education functions while overseeing cadre training and professional development  In addition  she leads  trains  and evaluates 230 cadets located at the Virginia Military Institute and the Virginia Women s Institute for Leadership  Maj Beaver enlisted in the Air Force in 1989 as a Communications Computer Systems Operator  She completed her bachelor s degree in Computer Science via the Airman Education and Commissioning Program and subsequently obtained her commission upon completion of Officer Training School in 2000  After she completed her initial Cyberspace Operations Officer training  she transferred to Germany where she served in various Communications Group and Squadron positions at Sembach and Ramstein Air Bases  She left Germany to pursue her master s degree in Computer Science at the Air Force Institute of Technology at Wright Patterson Air Force Base  Ohio  Upon graduating from the master s program  Maj Beaver transferred to Hurlburt Field  Florida where she worked on the Air Force Special Operations Command headquarters staff  The majority of her time on the special operations staff was spent in the Communications Plans and Programs branch and the Programming office  but she also performed Executive Officer duties for Lt Gen Bradley Heithold  Maj Beaver left Hurlburt Field to continue her service in support of the Air Force Intelligence  Surveillance  and Reconnaissance Agency at Lackland Air Force Base in San Antonio  Texas  While there  she served as the Chief of the Enterprise Management Branch within the Communications Directorate and the Deputy Chief of the Maintenance Division within the Directorate for Logistics  Installations  and Mission Support  Maj Beaver deployed in 2006 in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom  She spent the bulk of her deployed time at Joint Base Balad where she conducted interviews and collected information on recent and ongoing operations for United States Special Operations Command  Maj Beaver was selected for promotion to Lieutenant Colonel and expects to have the new rank on by the end of 2015  EDUCATION 2000 Bachelor of Science Degree  Computer Science  University of South Carolina  Columbia  SC 2001 Air and Space Basics Course  Maxwell AFB  AL 2005 Master of Science Degree  Computer Science  Air Force Institute of Technology  Wright Patterson AFB  OH 2006 Squadron Officer School  Maxwell AFB  AL 2013 Air Command and Staff College  Correspondence  ASSIGNMENTS 1  Dec 2000   Jun 2001  Support Flight Commander  886th Communications Squadron  Sembach Air Base  Germany 2  Jun 2001   May 2002  Officer in Charge  Information Systems Support Section  786th Communicatio