and the Programming office  but she also performed Executive Officer duties for Lt Gen Bradley Heithold  Maj Beaver left Hurlburt Field to continue her service in support of the Air Force Intelligence  Surveillance  and Reconnaissance Agency at Lackland Air Force Base in San Antonio  Texas  While there  she served as the Chief of the Enterprise Management Branch within the Communications Directorate and the Deputy Chief of the Maintenance Division within the Directorate for Logistics  Installations  and Mission Support  Maj Beaver deployed in 2006 in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom  She spent the bulk of her deployed time at Joint Base Balad where she conducted interviews and collected information on recent and ongoing operations for United States Special Operations Command  Maj Beaver was selected for promotion to Lieutenant Colonel and expects to have the new rank on by the end of 2015  EDUCATION 2000 Bachelor of Science Degree  Computer Science  University of South Carolina  Columbia  SC 2001 Air and Space Basics Course  Maxwell AFB  AL 2005 Master of Science Degree  Computer Science  Air Force Institute of Technology  Wright Patterson AFB  OH 2006 Squadron Officer School  Maxwell AFB  AL 2013 Air Command and Staff College  Correspondence  ASSIGNMENTS 1  Dec 2000   Jun 2001  Support Flight Commander  886th Communications Squadron  Sembach Air Base  Germany 2  Jun 2001   May 2002  Officer in Charge  Information Systems Support Section  786th Communications Squadron  Ramstein Air Base  Germany 3  May 2002   Aug 2003  Officer in Charge  Plans and Mobility  86th Communications Group  Ramstein Air Base  Germany 4  Aug 2003   Jun 2005  Student  Air Force Institute of Technology Masters Program  Wright Patterson AFB  OH 5  Jun 2005   Nov 2006  Officer in Charge  Requirements and Chief Information Officer Support  Communications Directorate  Air Force Special Operations Command  Hurlburt Field  FL 6  Nov 2006   Oct 2007  Chief  Command  Control  Communications  Comput