eted her bachelor s degree in Computer Science via the Airman Education and Commissioning Program and subsequently obtained her commission upon completion of Officer Training School in 2000  After she completed her initial Cyberspace Operations Officer training  she transferred to Germany where she served in various Communications Group and Squadron positions at Sembach and Ramstein Air Bases  She left Germany to pursue her master s degree in Computer Science at the Air Force Institute of Technology at Wright Patterson Air Force Base  Ohio  Upon graduating from the master s program  Maj Beaver transferred to Hurlburt Field  Florida where she worked on the Air Force Special Operations Command headquarters staff  The majority of her time on the special operations staff was spent in the Communications Plans and Programs branch and the Programming office  but she also performed Executive Officer duties for Lt Gen Bradley Heithold  Maj Beaver left Hurlburt Field to continue her service in support of the Air Force Intelligence  Surveillance  and Reconnaissance Agency at Lackland Air Force Base in San Antonio  Texas  While there  she served as the Chief of the Enterprise Management Branch within the Communications Directorate and the Deputy Chief of the Maintenance Division within the Directorate for Logistics  Installations  and Mission Support  Maj Beaver deployed in 2006 in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom  She spent the bulk of her deployed time at Joint Base Balad where she conducted interviews and collected information on recent and ongoing operations for United States Special Operations Command  Maj Beaver was selected for promotion to Lieutenant Colonel and expects to have the new rank on by the end of 2015  EDUCATION 2000 Bachelor of Science Degree  Computer Science  University of South Carolina  Columbia  SC 2001 Air and Space Basics Course  Maxwell AFB  AL 2005 Master of Science Degree  Computer Science  Air Force Institute of Technology  Wright Patterson AFB 